TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gerakos, Joseph
AU  - Linnainmaa, Juhani T.
T1  - Decomposing Value
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx118
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 31
IS  - 5
SP  - 1825
EP  - 1854
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Firms move between growth and value because of changes in either size or book value of equity. The value premium is specific to variation in book-to-market that emanates from size changes. A factor based on this variation earns the entire value premium; one based on the remaining variation earns no premium. Hence, not all high book-to-market firms earn the value premium, and some low book-to-market firms earn value-like returns. Many models price portfolios sorted by size and book-to-market. None distinguish firms that earn the value premium from those that have a high book-to-market but do not earn the premium.Received July 22, 2015; editorial decision June 29, 2017 by Editor Andrew Karolyi.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx118
ER  - 



